Guess who he was talking about.

122
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,360
If I really shot him dead tomorrow,

123
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:49,839
it would be a joke.

124
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:53,040
I heard you've broken shooting records.

125
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:54,519
It was long ago.

126
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:55,720
How can it be the same?

127
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,120
I think if Huang Zhixing knows

128
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,199
you'll be the one to fire,

129
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,399
no matter how big the risk,

130
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,399
he will be willing.

131
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:11,199
Someone has to fire this shot, right?

132
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:16,560
Alright then.

133
00:07:20,639 --> 00:07:21,920
I won't be the target anyway.

134
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:28,399
Don't worry yet.

135
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:29,839
We will have a better way.

136
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:30,879
It's too late.

137
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:32,240
The risk is too great.

138
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,160
Only this way

139
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,519
can we convince Cai Desheng.

140
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:35,959
But I think...

141
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,040
If you back out,

142
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,199
I'll do it myself.

143
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:39,680
Have you thought

144
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,079
that even if you're shot,

145
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:43,920
the Intelligence Agency will suspect
you staged it?

146
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:45,480
I know.

147
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,040
So I don't just get shot.

148
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,399
You need

149
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:51,079
to shoot me in the head.

150
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,879
His efforts were not in vain.

151
00:07:56,879 --> 00:07:58,079
We have successfully obtained

152
00:07:58,079 --> 00:07:59,360
the intel on the Eye Plan.

153
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,560
At the appropriate time,

154
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,720
I'll tell you

155
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,839
the details.

156
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,600
Chief Xu.

157
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,560
There is something I don't understand.

158
00:08:11,399 --> 00:08:12,759
We are always prepared

159
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:15,079
to sacrifice for our country.

160
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,279
That is reasonable.

161
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,560
If someone from the Chinese mainland

162
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,199
is willing to risk their lives

163
00:08:20,199 --> 00:08:21,519
for the unification,

164
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,800
that is understandable.

165
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:25,199
But Huang Zhixing
is born in Taiwan, China.

166
00:08:25,199 --> 00:08:27,079
He seeks nothing.

167
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,439
Clearly, he has a great future,

168
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,240
yet he'll risk his life

169
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,720
to help us stop the Eye Plan.

170
00:08:33,759 --> 00:08:34,799
Why?

171
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,240
What do you think?

172
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,759
I think there is a belief in his heart

173
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,639
that is different from ours.

174
00:08:45,759 --> 00:08:47,000
Indeed, it is different.

175
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:49,679
In fact, he has only one purpose.

176
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:50,759
What is it?

177
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,279
The national reunification.

178
00:08:53,759 --> 00:08:55,000
But we are not at war.

179
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,399
That's right.

180
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,679
His ambition stretches beyond now.

181
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,360
And the future.

182
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:04,879
He hopes the war

183
00:09:04,879 --> 00:09:07,279
will never break out in his hometown.

184
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:10,080
But he understands better
than most people

185
00:09:10,559 --> 00:09:11,440
that peace

186
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,200
is never taken for granted.

187
00:09:13,792 --> 00:09:18,976
(In treatment, do not disturb)

188
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:55,320
(My name is Huang Zhixing.)

189
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:57,519
(I'm born in Taiwan, China.)

190
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,759
(I was born in a veterans' village,)

191
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,559
(but I'm unlike many people around me.)

192
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,360
(Influenced by their families,)

193
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,840
(they say they are from Shandong,)

194
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:13,679
(Jiangsu, Fujian, or Guangdong.)

195
00:10:14,159 --> 00:10:15,600
(But I feel)

196
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,120
(that I'm born in Taiwan, China,)

197
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:18,720
(and here is my home.)

198
00:10:20,512 --> 00:10:22,432
- (I've never seen Chinese mainland.)
- Morning.

199
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:24,360
(Taiwan, China is my only home.)

200
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:30,360
(In this regard, my dad)

201
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,519
(was very rigid.)

202
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,559
(He always firmly believed)

203
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:37,200
(that he was displaced here.)

204
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,519
(Someday)

205
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:41,039
(he would return to the hometown.)

206
00:10:51,962 --> 00:11:00,032
(Want to return to the Chinese mainland)

207
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,840
(But actually,)

208
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,279
(he was only five when he came
to Taiwan, China.)

209
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:06,960
(He didn't remember)

210
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,480
(what the Chinese mainland was like.)

211
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,600
(Those so-called memories)

212
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,360
(were just imagination
based on the stories)

213
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,200
(told by my grandpa.)

214
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:30,559
(Grandpa passed away early.)

215
00:11:30,559 --> 00:11:32,000
(Those stories)

216
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,919
(became Dad's longing and solace.)

217
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:41,159
(Of course, Dad didn't agree
with my thoughts.)

218
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,120
(For that, I was beaten a lot
as a child.)

219
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,759
(But the more he beat me,
the more defiant I became.)

220
00:11:50,759 --> 00:11:52,200
(I had another new idea)

221
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,480
(that the future of Taiwan, China,)

222
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,559
(needed to be shaped by people like me.)

223
00:11:56,559 --> 00:11:58,240
(But my dad, who lived in the past,)

224
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,320
(would never understand this.)

225
00:12:04,559 --> 00:12:05,840
(When I was in my teens,)

226
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,200
(my mom passed away.)

227
00:12:07,679 --> 00:12:08,720
(Then I had no reason)

228
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,519
(to stay in this home anymore.)

229
00:12:11,559 --> 00:12:13,120
(So after being admitted to college,)

230
00:12:13,639 --> 00:12:15,159
(I completely left here.)

231
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,679
(In college,)

232
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,440
(I met more like-minded peers.)

233
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,240
(Communication with them)

234
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:29,559
(stimulated my desire to see
the outside world.)

235
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:36,768
(So I used the money I saved
from part-time jobs)

236
00:12:37,184 --> 00:12:39,200
(Transportation tickets)
(to travel on a budget everywhere.)

237
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,639
(I thought)

238
00:12:40,639 --> 00:12:43,039
(that if I went to various places,)

239
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:44,039
(maybe)

240
00:12:44,039 --> 00:12:47,200
(I could have a clearer idea
of the future of Taiwan, China.)

241
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:50,120
(Later on, by chance,)

242
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:53,559
(Exchange Program Notice)
(my university has an exchange slot.)

243
00:12:53,559 --> 00:12:54,919
(It suddenly occurred to me)

244
00:12:54,919 --> 00:12:57,960
(that I had been to Europe, America,
and Japan,)

245
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:00,759
(but I had never thought of going to
the Chinese mainland.)

246
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:04,879
(Just like that,)

247
00:13:04,896 --> 00:13:05,639
(Application Form)

248
00:13:05,639 --> 00:13:08,279
(I finally came to the hometown
my dad mentioned.)

249
00:13:09,792 --> 00:13:11,080
(World Map)

250
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,519
(I'm indeed born in Taiwan, China,)

251
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,759
(and have many differences with people)

252
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:16,120
(on the Chinese mainland.)

253
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:18,639
(But we speak the same language,)

254
00:13:18,919 --> 00:13:20,399
(cherish the same heritage,)

255
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:21,799
(and bleed the same blood.)

256
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,840
(Our similarities)

257
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,519
(matter most.)

258
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,080
(Until that time,)

259
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,159
(looking back at my dad's words,)

260
00:13:30,559 --> 00:13:32,000
(I find that perhaps)

261
00:13:32,519 --> 00:13:34,080
(he was not entirely wrong.)

262
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:37,840
(Life went on.)

263
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,559
(Degree,)

264
00:13:38,559 --> 00:13:39,559
(job,)

265
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:41,039
(and the steady climb.)

266
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,879
(But I found that in Taiwan, China,)

267
00:13:42,879 --> 00:13:44,679
(clean hands won't take me to the top.)

268
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:45,399
(Just right,)

269
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,559
(a friend)

270
00:13:46,559 --> 00:13:48,159
(had made a name in the gang.)

271
00:13:48,159 --> 00:13:49,639
(So I went to him.)

272
00:14:13,024 --> 00:14:14,976
(Straits Exchange Foundation)

273
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,720
(The birth of my daughter)

274
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,360
(once again changed my attitude
towards the world.)

275
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:36,360
(Before she was born,)

276
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,600
(I felt that the world was a stage.)

277
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,639
(The more chaotic it was,)

278
00:14:39,639 --> 00:14:40,960
(the more chances I would have.)

279
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:43,200
(But after having her,)

280
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,679
(I only wish for world peace.)

